Introductory course
- to acquaint students of computer science with the problems and methods of informatics and its applications, as well as professional career opportunities,
- lectures and seminars help students to acquire the necessary skills to be encountered while studying at university. The course provides an overview of learning styles and coping with them, as well as the nature of group work. Students are helped to deal with self-analysis, coping with stress and problematic situations, and are introduced to academic practices.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give to students - an overview of different areas of informatics and its applications, and possible directions of specialization, - an overview of different learning styles and skills, time consumption and learning motivation,  - experience in creating academic text and in public performance in seminar,  - experience in learning time scheduling  - basic skills necessary for learning computer science.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student  - has obtained an overview of the different areas of informatics and its possible directions of specialization, - knows his/her opportunities and peculiarities as a student and is able to rely on them when studying at the university, - consciously and expediently plans his/her studies at the university and draws up his/her study plan for the entire study period, - uses general and specialty-specific learning techniques, chooses the learning method corresponding to his/her goals in the context of the subject, becomes aware of working and non-working learning styles for himself/herself and fellow students based on previous experience, - is able to find motivation for learning and analyze one's use of time, - is able to formulate a simple academic text and has experience in presenting, - participates in group work in the development of a simple web application using version control software, - gets acquainted with the work of a research group of the institute or company and analyzes his/her learning needs and career opportunities as an IT specialist.
